WEBVTT

00:00.332 --> 00:01.300
<i>Previously on "The Whispers..."</i>

00:01.377 --> 00:04.854
Drill, I want you to leave my daughter
alone. I'll do whatever it takes.

00:05.130 --> 00:08.583
Drill says if you do what the letters
say, he'll give you what you want.

00:08.667 --> 00:11.169
Drill's been here before, back in 1982.

00:11.303 --> 00:13.387
My son Thomas, he killed his brother.

00:13.505 --> 00:15.006
Said Drill made him do it.

00:15.140 --> 00:16.224
Thomas, we are here

00:16.341 --> 00:17.391
because we want to help our son.

00:17.509 --> 00:19.427
They must have sent another one.

00:19.511 --> 00:21.178
He can't be the same friend I had!

00:21.263 --> 00:22.897
- Why not, Thomas?
- Because I killed him!

00:23.015 --> 00:24.482
[Door opens]

00:24.566 --> 00:25.933
No!

00:26.018 --> 00:27.068
Thomas.

00:27.185 --> 00:29.186
He knows how to kill Drill.

00:35.010 --> 00:36.827
[Thunder rumbles]

00:36.912 --> 00:38.162
Thomas!

00:38.263 --> 00:39.263
Eliot!

00:39.314 --> 00:41.432
Where are you?!

00:44.970 --> 00:46.737
Eliot!

00:46.838 --> 00:48.372
Thomas!

00:50.008 --> 00:53.477
[Thunder rumbles]

00:53.578 --> 00:54.895
Thomas!

00:54.980 --> 00:57.081
[Breathing heavily] Okay.

00:57.132 --> 00:59.700
Where's Eliot?

01:01.887 --> 01:03.354
Where's all this blood coming from?!

01:03.421 --> 01:04.355
[Thunder rumbles]

01:04.422 --> 01:06.073
Thomas!

01:06.191 --> 01:07.358
He made me do it, daddy!

01:07.459 --> 01:08.626
I had to!

01:08.727 --> 01:10.127
I had to!

01:10.228 --> 01:11.929
Eliot!

01:12.030 --> 01:13.097
Eliot!

01:13.164 --> 01:15.299
Man: We have a gunshot wound here!

01:22.207 --> 01:23.407
Thank you.

01:23.475 --> 01:24.558
You didn't give me much
detail on the phone.

01:24.643 --> 01:25.793
I know.

01:25.910 --> 01:27.177
What is he doing here?

01:27.278 --> 01:28.279
Security!

01:28.346 --> 01:29.747
I can explain... stay away from me.

01:29.749 --> 01:32.316
It's okay, Dr. Benavidez,
he is no longer a threat.

01:32.350 --> 01:34.017
He knows who he is.
His name is Sean Bennigan.

01:34.102 --> 01:35.252
He is my husband.

01:36.788 --> 01:38.389
Your... your husband is...

01:38.456 --> 01:39.640
yes. I know, we have a lot
of explaining to do,

01:39.724 --> 01:42.392
but right now, that man
we brought in here, please...

01:42.494 --> 01:45.095
Please. You can't let him die.

01:48.566 --> 01:50.901
Jessup: Thanks, Frank.
I appreciate you trying.

01:50.985 --> 01:52.236
It's too late.

01:52.287 --> 01:54.771
One of the neighbors already
called in the gunshots.

01:54.856 --> 01:57.574
My contact at the bureau
wasn't able to bury it.

01:57.642 --> 01:58.775
So, what does that mean?

01:58.810 --> 02:00.944
Local policemen start canvassing
the hospitals.

02:00.946 --> 02:03.447
It's only a matter of time
before they get here.

02:03.514 --> 02:05.382
Lena: Wes, I shot a man.

02:05.416 --> 02:07.818
You were protecting Minx.
It's what I would have done.

02:07.886 --> 02:09.586
It's what any parent would have done.

02:09.654 --> 02:11.038
But I didn't protect her.

02:11.089 --> 02:13.523
And now I'm sitting here
half-hoping that man might die.

02:13.608 --> 02:15.292
What kind of a person does that?

02:15.376 --> 02:16.693
Okay, okay.

02:21.466 --> 02:23.500
Maria: We were able to stabilize him.

02:23.584 --> 02:25.335
Claire: So he's gonna make it?

02:25.436 --> 02:26.903
It's too early to say.

02:27.004 --> 02:28.638
He's lost a lot of blood.

02:28.723 --> 02:29.906
When can we speak to him?

02:29.957 --> 02:31.174
He's still unconscious.

02:31.242 --> 02:34.711
We don't know when he's going to come out.

02:35.763 --> 02:36.813
Wes.

02:41.035 --> 02:44.838
Do not tell Minx what I did.

02:44.872 --> 02:48.408
Tell her my mom's sick.
Tell her anything but the truth.

02:48.492 --> 02:50.176
Officers, it's me you want to speak to.

02:50.261 --> 02:51.311
What? Wes.

02:51.395 --> 02:52.996
I will take care of this.

02:53.080 --> 02:56.066
No. There are favors I can call in, okay?

02:56.200 --> 02:57.834
Officer: Sir, come with me.

02:57.902 --> 02:59.519
Wait. I want to escort my husband.

02:59.604 --> 03:01.838
Ma'am, we can't let you ride in
the car with him.

03:01.872 --> 03:03.440
I'm not leaving him.

03:03.541 --> 03:05.125
Fine.

03:05.209 --> 03:06.476
You take her.

03:10.231 --> 03:11.848
[Sighs]

03:11.916 --> 03:13.817
What do we do? I can't...

03:13.851 --> 03:15.018
I can't just sit here doing nothing,

03:15.119 --> 03:16.686
praying for Thomas to recover.

03:16.721 --> 03:18.571
- What choice do we have?
- We can keep looking.

03:18.656 --> 03:20.690
He may be the only one
who knows how to kill Drill,

03:20.725 --> 03:22.625
but that doesn't mean
that he kept it to himself.

03:22.710 --> 03:23.960
His house, he... he might have

03:24.028 --> 03:25.695
written it down somewhere, kept a journal.

03:25.763 --> 03:27.197
We can't leave him here unprotected.

03:27.264 --> 03:28.364
Jessup: He won't be.

03:28.449 --> 03:29.749
I'll stay.

03:29.800 --> 03:32.018
Besides, this is the last place
either one of you should be.

03:32.102 --> 03:33.870
The police found us,
so you can be damn sure

03:33.938 --> 03:35.605
Frommer's men will be sniffing around, too.

03:35.689 --> 03:37.707
He's right. We need to keep moving.

03:39.310 --> 03:40.360
Jessup.

03:40.394 --> 03:42.178
The minute Thomas wakes up, I'll call you.

03:42.213 --> 03:43.646
You have my word.

03:48.018 --> 03:49.736
Hey.

03:49.820 --> 03:50.820
Hey. What is it?

03:50.954 --> 03:52.055
It's just Thomas.

03:52.089 --> 03:54.490
We led Drill right to him.

03:54.525 --> 03:57.260
Everything he's been through...

03:57.311 --> 03:59.028
- He doesn't deserve that.
- [Siren chirps]

03:59.113 --> 04:02.015
[Tires screech]

04:09.623 --> 04:11.557
[Indistinct talking]

04:14.194 --> 04:15.344
Wes!

04:15.429 --> 04:16.678
Lena?

04:16.730 --> 04:17.697
Open this door!

04:17.815 --> 04:19.115
Lena!

04:19.199 --> 04:20.315
Lena, it's gonna be okay!

04:20.384 --> 04:21.684
Lena! Wes?

04:21.718 --> 04:24.620
Get your hands off me!
Lena, I will take care of this!

04:24.755 --> 04:26.556
What's going on here?

04:26.640 --> 04:28.524
Explain to me what is going on here.

04:28.609 --> 04:29.809
It's okay!

