05:02.005 --> 05:03.372
Jessup: First we need to remove

05:03.456 --> 05:04.957
all electrical devices from the room.

05:05.074 --> 05:07.326
He has to be monitored.
He needs his medications.

05:07.410 --> 05:09.545
Then we've got to do it
the old-fashioned way.

05:09.629 --> 05:11.246
I'm pretty sure we had hospitals

05:11.347 --> 05:12.915
before we had all these machines.

05:13.049 --> 05:16.301
Then how about you tell me
what's really going on?

05:16.419 --> 05:19.304
Until then, I am not breaking
hospital protocol

05:19.422 --> 05:21.423
or risking my patient's life.

05:26.512 --> 05:27.896
You said it yourself,

05:27.981 --> 05:30.649
back at the nuclear power plant.

05:30.767 --> 05:32.351
What's happening only makes sense

05:32.435 --> 05:34.436
if you're willing to admit the impossible.

05:34.520 --> 05:36.772
And you know what I'm
talking about, don't you?

05:39.943 --> 05:41.877
Thomas Harcourt may be the only person

05:41.978 --> 05:44.363
who knows how to get rid of...
Whatever is here.

05:44.447 --> 05:46.281
If he dies...

05:51.921 --> 05:54.289
What else do we need to do?

05:54.373 --> 05:57.042
Clear this wing of all
patients and personnel.

05:57.126 --> 05:58.960
Okay.

05:59.095 --> 06:00.879
There's one last thing.

06:00.963 --> 06:04.182
I need to see your children's ward.

06:06.552 --> 06:08.970
The three of you certainly
know how to cause trouble.

06:09.105 --> 06:10.555
I have to give you that.

06:10.640 --> 06:11.973
Sir... no, it's one thing

06:12.058 --> 06:13.725
to pull rank on a full local cops.

06:13.809 --> 06:15.644
It's another thing to keep them quiet

06:15.728 --> 06:17.362
once they find out what the hell
you people have been up to.

06:17.480 --> 06:18.530
I can explain.

06:18.648 --> 06:19.981
Oh, that's exactly what I'm afraid of.

06:20.066 --> 06:25.537
Can't have you out there saying
God knows what to God knows who.

06:25.655 --> 06:27.038
Mrs. Bennigan,

06:27.156 --> 06:30.325
I would say it's a pleasure to
finally make your acquaintance,

06:30.409 --> 06:32.160
but we both know I'd be lying.

06:33.496 --> 06:34.746
Likewise, sir.

06:34.830 --> 06:36.498
I understand you're upset about your son.

06:36.632 --> 06:37.799
But that's over now,

06:37.883 --> 06:39.918
because each of you will be
taken a facility

06:40.002 --> 06:41.903
where you'll be held until further notice.

06:42.004 --> 06:43.722
So you're gonna lock up the only people

06:43.839 --> 06:45.006
who know how to end this?

06:45.141 --> 06:46.174
Excuse me?

06:46.258 --> 06:47.592
We have a lead.

06:47.676 --> 06:49.394
Someone who knows how to destroy Drill.

06:49.512 --> 06:50.562
Mrs. Bennigan...

06:50.679 --> 06:52.430
<i>Agent</i> Bennigan.

06:52.515 --> 06:55.500
Agent Bennigan, this desperate ploy...

06:55.618 --> 06:57.185
you're right.

06:57.319 --> 06:58.953
I am desperate.

06:59.038 --> 07:01.489
I am desperate because...

07:01.574 --> 07:05.893
My child, because all...

07:05.995 --> 07:08.246
all of our children are in this.

07:08.330 --> 07:11.149
And if you think that
I am just gonna sit back

07:11.233 --> 07:13.868
and watch them become casualties, you know,

07:13.953 --> 07:15.937
the truth is that you
wouldn't have any idea

07:16.021 --> 07:18.373
what you were dealing with
if it weren't for us.

07:18.457 --> 07:20.742
You need us.

07:20.826 --> 07:22.794
And you know it.

07:26.782 --> 07:29.050
This lead you all think you have...

07:29.101 --> 07:32.537
Sean: There's a credible witness
that believes the entity

07:32.621 --> 07:34.472
we're dealing with today is
actually a second visitor.

07:34.556 --> 07:37.091
Wes: 1982... he was neutralized

07:37.176 --> 07:39.193
before he could become a threat.

07:39.228 --> 07:41.162
Please do not waste time
making us the enemy.

07:41.196 --> 07:44.098
The real enemy is out there plotting
his next move against all of us.

07:44.183 --> 07:47.068
We do not have time.

07:52.841 --> 07:54.141
24 hours.

07:54.192 --> 07:57.278
And I want updates 'round the clock.

08:08.690 --> 08:10.524
He let us go. What?

08:10.659 --> 08:11.826
What about the shooting?

08:11.910 --> 08:13.244
He's taking care of it.

08:13.362 --> 08:14.912
Just like that?

08:15.030 --> 08:17.081
Well, with guys like him,
nothing is "just like that,"

08:17.199 --> 08:18.916
but it beats the hell out
of the alternative.

08:19.034 --> 08:21.035
I'll have someone drive you home.

08:21.169 --> 08:23.120
Wes, no. You'll be safe, okay?

08:23.205 --> 08:26.006
I'll have thermal cameras
put all over the house.

08:26.091 --> 08:28.459
No, Wes, I am not going into hiding.

08:28.543 --> 08:29.793
This is my fight, too.

08:29.878 --> 08:31.595
Minx needs you, Lena.

08:31.680 --> 08:34.715
What Minx needs is for this to be over.

08:34.850 --> 08:36.049
Please.

08:36.134 --> 08:38.385
Let me do something.

08:38.470 --> 08:40.321
Claire: I know.

08:40.388 --> 08:42.857
Go back to the hospital
and make sure Thomas is safe.

08:42.941 --> 08:44.441
I'll head to his house. Alone?

08:44.559 --> 08:46.227
Lena: Not alone.

08:46.361 --> 08:48.562
Wes and I will take her.

08:51.283 --> 08:53.701
Woman: Good job. [Speaking indistinctly]

08:56.237 --> 08:59.623
So, it looks like we have 14 patients right

08:59.741 --> 09:01.825
the nurses need to make sure each child

09:01.910 --> 09:03.577
is accounted for at all times.

09:03.712 --> 09:06.330
Okay. I'll... I'll go talk to them.

09:22.313 --> 09:23.680
[Woman sobbing]

09:46.829 --> 09:49.464
So, it's just a coincidence that

09:49.531 --> 09:52.200
Frommer's guys nab us
just as we're leaving,

09:52.301 --> 09:55.269
just as you advised us to do?

09:55.370 --> 09:57.605
You know what?

09:57.673 --> 09:59.841
I'm done trying to prove myself to you.

09:59.875 --> 10:01.776
You don't have kids, do you?

10:01.810 --> 10:02.977
No. My wife,

10:03.045 --> 10:04.645
my soon-to-be ex-wife,

10:04.713 --> 10:07.281
said she didn't want to have any.

10:07.349 --> 10:09.984
Funny thing, though. She's pregnant now.

10:10.035 --> 10:11.819
Sorry.

10:14.856 --> 10:16.123
But I get what you're saying.

10:16.191 --> 10:18.359
If it was my kid... Though I suppose

10:18.443 --> 10:20.361
he's somebody's son, too.

10:20.429 --> 10:22.897
He could be lying, you know.

10:22.948 --> 10:24.799
Or crazy.

10:24.866 --> 10:26.834
We can't be sure that he really knows

10:26.868 --> 10:28.602
how to kill Drill.

10:28.637 --> 10:30.321
He's got to know something.

10:30.405 --> 10:33.023
Otherwise, why would Drill be after him?

10:37.779 --> 10:39.630
It's quiet.

10:43.502 --> 10:44.468
Too quiet.

10:44.553 --> 10:47.688
Gonna take a look around.

10:47.789 --> 10:50.724
You good?

10:50.809 --> 10:51.959
Mm.

11:10.078 --> 11:15.983
It's incredible, the amount
of work he put into this.

11:16.034 --> 11:20.454
My dad and I used to make models.

11:20.522 --> 11:22.723
I mean, nothing like this, but...

11:22.774 --> 11:24.925
They're my best memories growing up.

11:27.645 --> 11:30.898
You never told me that before.

11:30.932 --> 11:34.968
Yeah, strange, it... I... I guess
this never came up.

11:35.053 --> 11:37.571
What are we looking for, exactly?

11:37.655 --> 11:40.724
Uh, notes, folded-down pages in books,

11:40.809 --> 11:42.009
anything to do with electricity,

11:42.076 --> 11:43.544
anything to do with his childhood.

11:45.680 --> 11:47.447
I may have found something.

11:51.069 --> 11:53.937
It looks like it was taken
at the institution.

11:54.022 --> 11:56.373
Imagine celebrating your
birthday in a place like that.

11:56.457 --> 11:58.308
And not just one.

11:58.393 --> 12:00.494
He spent 10 birthdays there.

12:04.198 --> 12:05.299
"Remember, it takes only

12:05.400 --> 12:07.184
one candle to battle the darkness."

12:08.736 --> 12:10.637
Whoever took this picture,

12:10.738 --> 12:13.023
he cared enough about as
to celebrate his birthday.

12:13.141 --> 12:14.274
Maybe he was a doctor there.

12:14.308 --> 12:16.209
Maybe he still is.

12:16.244 --> 12:18.679
He might have therapy tapes, patient files.

12:18.763 --> 12:19.679
We need to find him.

12:19.781 --> 12:21.414
I agree. Let's... let's go.

12:24.352 --> 12:26.403
[Footsteps]

12:33.795 --> 12:35.495
Come on, Thomas.

12:35.596 --> 12:37.430
What do you know?

12:46.490 --> 12:48.842
I could step outside if you need to...

12:48.926 --> 12:50.260
No. It's okay.

12:50.344 --> 12:52.946
You sure?

12:53.080 --> 12:54.597
I'm fine.

12:54.682 --> 12:56.866
Maria, I needed someone to see

12:56.951 --> 12:58.551
what was happening to me,

12:58.586 --> 13:01.488
to stop me in case I did something.

13:01.555 --> 13:03.289
I am sorry.

13:03.391 --> 13:05.358
But you remember everything now?

13:05.409 --> 13:07.560
Yeah.

13:07.661 --> 13:09.963
The good <i> and</i> the bad.

13:12.666 --> 13:14.300
What was it like

13:14.302 --> 13:17.086
to just get it all back?

13:17.171 --> 13:20.523
It was like I was
a completely different person

13:20.608 --> 13:22.575
in the blink of an eye.

13:22.660 --> 13:28.315
But the Sean Bennigan that
crashed in that jet was gone.

13:29.483 --> 13:31.951
I've seen too much in the last few months.

13:32.019 --> 13:34.754
Too much has happened.

13:34.822 --> 13:37.440
Ever since that night,

13:37.524 --> 13:39.792
what happened at the reactor...

13:39.877 --> 13:42.695
I haven't been able to sleep, to eat.

13:42.763 --> 13:43.830
What I saw...

13:43.881 --> 13:45.832
I know.

13:45.899 --> 13:47.834
Imagine living with that feeling every day

13:47.935 --> 13:49.218
for the last three months.

13:49.303 --> 13:51.404
That was my life.

13:52.533 --> 13:55.601
I know that he knows
what I'm talking about.

13:55.686 --> 13:58.655
Only he has it much worse.

13:58.756 --> 14:01.391
Me, I got some version of my life back.

14:01.492 --> 14:03.860
But him?

14:03.961 --> 14:06.429
His childhood, his future,

14:06.530 --> 14:10.800
everything was taken away from him.

14:10.851 --> 14:13.870
I won't let that happen to my son.

14:15.122 --> 14:18.274
We're looking for information
about a former patient.

14:18.308 --> 14:20.343
He was here from '82 to '92.

14:20.410 --> 14:23.212
Are there any doctors or...
or staff members

14:23.280 --> 14:24.580
who may have been around then?

14:24.615 --> 14:27.049
With the turnover as it is
at this place, you'd be lucky

14:27.100 --> 14:29.185
to find someone who's been here
more than two.

14:29.253 --> 14:31.153
- Okay, what about records?
- Delaware law, honey.

14:31.221 --> 14:32.855
Seven years is all we're required to keep.

14:35.025 --> 14:36.959
How about this?

14:37.010 --> 14:40.830
You have any idea where room might be?

14:40.897 --> 14:43.132
All I know is that before the remodel

14:43.266 --> 14:44.467
a few years ago,

14:44.568 --> 14:48.170
the kids' wing used to be
on the second floor.

14:48.255 --> 14:49.855
But that was before my time.

14:49.940 --> 14:52.324
Thank you. Thank you.

14:52.409 --> 14:54.126
Anything?

14:54.244 --> 14:56.512
I don't know.

14:56.563 --> 15:00.249
Thomas called this place home for 10 years.

15:00.317 --> 15:01.767
People keep their secrets at home.

15:04.871 --> 15:06.622
[Elevator bell dings]

15:27.727 --> 15:29.695
Are you sick?

15:31.414 --> 15:32.948
No.

15:35.151 --> 15:36.185
Someone I know is.

15:36.286 --> 15:39.588
My brother's sick.

15:39.622 --> 15:40.789
It's his heart.

15:40.890 --> 15:42.391
Doesn't work anymore.

15:44.194 --> 15:45.577
Sorry to hear that.

15:45.662 --> 15:49.248
I'm gonna make him the best mask ever.

15:49.332 --> 15:51.550
Maybe it will make him smile again.

15:55.088 --> 15:57.339
[Elevator thuds]

16:01.811 --> 16:03.178
Are we stuck?

16:03.313 --> 16:04.429
Is the air gonna go out?

16:04.514 --> 16:05.564
It's gonna be okay.

16:09.652 --> 16:10.853
Hello?

16:10.937 --> 16:12.437
[Clicking]

16:12.522 --> 16:13.522
Hello?

16:13.623 --> 16:16.608
[Electricity crackling]

16:24.309 --> 16:25.876
So, this is the old children's wing.

16:40.558 --> 16:42.259
[Breathes deeply]

16:50.542 --> 16:52.943
Lena?

16:58.181 --> 17:00.649
For what it's worth...

17:00.717 --> 17:04.153
I know how it feels...

17:04.186 --> 17:07.289
To have done something that you...

17:07.357 --> 17:09.425
You wish you could take back.

17:15.064 --> 17:18.099
I was protecting my daughter.

17:18.167 --> 17:20.102
What's your excuse?

17:23.173 --> 17:25.207
Wes: Claire?

17:25.258 --> 17:27.576
You need to see this.

17:36.052 --> 17:37.135
Here.

17:46.312 --> 17:49.314
Wes: It's not quite the same angle,
but it's one of these rooms.

17:49.399 --> 17:51.466
I'll check upstairs.

17:51.567 --> 17:53.935
I'll start with the next one.

17:57.607 --> 18:01.309
[Television playing indistinctly]

18:18.194 --> 18:19.327
What is it?

18:19.428 --> 18:20.428
It's Jessup.

18:20.463 --> 18:22.063
They found him unconscious in the elevator.

18:22.198 --> 18:23.698
Someone injected him with sodium pentothal.

18:23.766 --> 18:25.951
- Is he okay?
- Yeah. Luckily, it wasn't a lethal dose,

18:25.985 --> 18:28.803
but it might be some time
before he's back on his feet.

18:28.854 --> 18:29.771
Where was he injected?

18:29.855 --> 18:31.406
Uh... Where?

18:31.507 --> 18:32.774
The thigh, I think.

18:32.808 --> 18:35.243
So about the same height as a child?

18:35.294 --> 18:36.411
What are you saying?

18:36.545 --> 18:37.946
Drill's here.

18:38.013 --> 18:39.280
We need to move him right now.

18:39.348 --> 18:41.203
- Where?
- Somewhere where we can

18:41.228 --> 18:42.891
control the electricity.

18:42.952 --> 18:44.786
Okay, I know where to go.

18:48.190 --> 18:50.458
[Television playing indistinctly]

18:53.145 --> 18:55.163
Excuse me.

18:56.565 --> 18:58.666
Excuse me.

19:00.653 --> 19:03.838
Do you mind if I just look out your window?

19:14.733 --> 19:16.150
Wes!

19:21.890 --> 19:23.257
This is it.

19:52.888 --> 19:53.921
[Panting]

19:53.972 --> 19:55.606
We should be safe down here.

20:11.256 --> 20:14.408
[Blood-pressure cuff pumping]

20:14.493 --> 20:16.310
His pressure is dangerously low.

20:16.361 --> 20:17.945
Okay, just keep him stable.

20:17.996 --> 20:20.598
I'm gonna find a circuit
breaker, shut the power down.

20:20.716 --> 20:22.500
Hey. Just keep him alive.

20:22.617 --> 20:23.918
I'll be right back.

20:28.774 --> 20:30.241
Thomas.

20:30.292 --> 20:32.593
Thomas, can you hear me?

20:32.694 --> 20:33.861
Thomas.

20:33.929 --> 20:38.466
Rabbi: Can you hear me?

20:38.500 --> 20:41.702
Those must be some heavy
thoughts you're carrying.

20:41.753 --> 20:44.688
I assume you came here to unload
some of that burden.

20:44.773 --> 20:46.106
Sorry I'm late. I had some trouble...

20:46.208 --> 20:48.175
no, no, I-I'm sorry. I was just, uh...

20:48.210 --> 20:50.744
Do not deny yourself of
what you know you must do.

20:50.829 --> 20:53.230
Please. Sit.

21:01.723 --> 21:04.508
[Sighs]

21:04.592 --> 21:07.594
Patient or visitor?

21:07.662 --> 21:09.229
Honestly, I'm not sure.

21:09.297 --> 21:10.998
Believe it or not, I hear a lot of that

21:11.032 --> 21:16.704
around here. [Chuckles]

21:17.305 --> 21:19.706
I did something.

21:19.774 --> 21:22.076
Something that in a million years

21:22.160 --> 21:23.944
I never thought I could do.

21:23.978 --> 21:28.515
I keep telling myself it was
to protect my daughter, but I...

21:28.616 --> 21:29.866
I did it.

21:29.951 --> 21:33.487
I crossed that line, and...

21:34.789 --> 21:36.123
And now I don't know...

21:36.224 --> 21:39.893
you don't know how you'll go back.

21:39.927 --> 21:43.463
I'm sorry to tell you that you can't.

21:46.134 --> 21:47.401
So what do I do?

21:47.468 --> 21:49.436
You must find a way to make amends,

21:49.520 --> 21:51.872
to take responsibility.

21:51.940 --> 21:53.056
How?

21:53.141 --> 21:57.010
That is between you and your God.

21:57.095 --> 21:58.612
You don't need to light all the candles

21:58.680 --> 22:00.047
to see your way out of the darkness.

22:00.098 --> 22:02.282
It just starts with one.

22:03.751 --> 22:04.885
Wait. What did you say?

22:04.919 --> 22:06.153
I'm sorry?

22:06.187 --> 22:07.754
About the candle.

22:07.855 --> 22:09.789
It's just something I like to tell

22:09.874 --> 22:11.224
the patients around here.

22:11.309 --> 22:13.326
You took that photo.

22:13.377 --> 22:14.828
I... I don't follow.

22:14.929 --> 22:17.464
You knew Thomas.

22:17.565 --> 22:19.833
My God. What's he done now?

22:19.901 --> 22:21.184
Wes: There's nothing here.

22:21.269 --> 22:24.304
If this was Thomas' room,
it's all gone now.

22:26.524 --> 22:27.574
What's this?

22:27.608 --> 22:29.292
What?

22:30.511 --> 22:32.279
There's a mirror.

22:35.566 --> 22:36.650
It was right here.

22:38.419 --> 22:42.188
Looks like someone drew something.

22:51.031 --> 22:56.569
The eyes... sometimes I think
they're still following me

22:56.604 --> 22:57.971
in the dark.

23:00.040 --> 23:03.059
There's something there.

23:06.964 --> 23:09.349
You're going to make the voices come back.

23:09.483 --> 23:10.867
Don't! Don't! Don't!

23:10.985 --> 23:13.253
Don't! Don't! Don't! Don't! Don't!

23:13.337 --> 23:15.321
What's going on here?

23:15.356 --> 23:16.573
Don't! Don't! Make them stop!

23:16.657 --> 23:18.041
- Who are you people?
- Make them stop!

23:18.158 --> 23:20.126
Make them stop! I'm calling security.

23:20.211 --> 23:23.830
It's okay. He already tried
to escape once before!

23:23.914 --> 23:26.132
[Sobbing]

23:34.575 --> 23:37.860
Wes: What is it?

23:37.945 --> 23:39.996
- I think it's...
- Rabbi: It's the Dybbuk.

23:41.915 --> 23:43.599
Lena: This is Rabbi Ezra.

23:43.717 --> 23:45.651
He's the one who took the photo.

23:47.838 --> 23:48.805
Rabbi, what... what is this dybbuk?

23:48.922 --> 23:50.022
It's the evil spirit

23:50.107 --> 23:52.625
that cleaves unto the soul, and on it does,

23:52.709 --> 23:55.261
it never lets go.

24:10.978 --> 24:12.328
Michael.

24:12.412 --> 24:15.381
Drill says you can wake up now.

24:15.449 --> 24:18.818
[Air hissing]

24:18.919 --> 24:20.519
[Monitor beeping]

24:29.613 --> 24:31.864
[Beeping stops]

24:35.202 --> 24:36.168
Hi.

24:36.253 --> 24:37.470
Shh!

24:44.711 --> 24:46.846
Now it's your turn.

24:49.146 --> 24:51.190
The doctors here, they couldn't
get through to Thomas.

24:51.610 --> 24:53.077
He refused to talk about
what happened that night,

24:53.145 --> 24:54.345
said they would never believe him.

24:54.396 --> 24:55.446
But he talked to you?

24:55.514 --> 24:56.965
Well, he showed up at my office one day,

24:57.049 --> 24:59.517
said he'd come across the story
of the Dybbuk

24:59.585 --> 25:01.534
and wanted to learn more.

25:01.914 --> 25:03.364
Wes: And what did you tell him?

25:03.449 --> 25:04.715
I told him it was just a story

25:04.800 --> 25:07.618
passed down from generation to generation.

25:07.720 --> 25:09.387
Thomas...

25:09.471 --> 25:11.706
He said I was wrong...

25:11.790 --> 25:14.142
[Indistinct talking]

25:14.226 --> 25:16.527
[Indistinct talking on P.A. System]

25:16.578 --> 25:19.981
that it wasn't just a story...

25:20.065 --> 25:22.550
For the Dybbuk was real.

25:33.979 --> 25:37.848
And once he had chosen his body...

25:40.485 --> 25:42.103
he would never be able to leave.

25:42.187 --> 25:44.038
[Monitor beeping]

25:44.122 --> 25:46.173
What's happening? We're losing him.
He's going into shock.

25:46.258 --> 25:47.775
- What do you need?
- A ventilator,

25:47.893 --> 25:48.959
epinephrine shot.

25:49.061 --> 25:51.462
I'll go. Where do I find it?

25:51.563 --> 25:54.198
Lena: So that's Thomas carrying Drill?

25:54.299 --> 25:55.850
Wes: That tree, I've...

25:55.934 --> 25:57.735
I've seen it before in the diorama.

25:57.819 --> 26:00.471
Why draw it here? I mean, what does it...

26:00.505 --> 26:04.058
because...He's trying
to tell us what happened.

26:04.092 --> 26:06.544
He's trying to tell us that's...

26:06.611 --> 26:08.445
That's not Thomas.

26:21.660 --> 26:22.693
It's Eliot.

26:22.744 --> 26:24.128
Rabbi: Till the last day he was here,

26:24.195 --> 26:25.946
Thomas insisted he was innocent
of his brother's murder.

26:26.031 --> 26:28.432
Maybe Thomas was telling the truth.

26:28.516 --> 26:31.168
What if Thomas didn't kill Eliot?

26:31.219 --> 26:33.704
Well, if... if he didn't, then who...

26:33.772 --> 26:35.255
Drill.

26:35.340 --> 26:37.274
Thomas wasn't Drill's only friend.

26:37.309 --> 26:39.076
Drill was talking to Eliot, too.

26:39.127 --> 26:40.728
Remember, Thomas... he said... he said

26:40.812 --> 26:42.246
he refused to send out the signal

26:42.313 --> 26:44.298
because he knew what
would happen if he did, so...

26:44.382 --> 26:45.933
so Drill convinced Eliot
to help him instead.

26:46.017 --> 26:47.484
Oh, I think he did more than convince him.

26:47.535 --> 26:51.321
The story of the Dybbuk...

26:51.406 --> 26:54.424
It's a possession story.

26:54.509 --> 26:58.128
So you think Drill took Eliot's body?

26:58.213 --> 27:00.747
Yes.

27:00.832 --> 27:02.382
So, that night in the woods...

27:02.467 --> 27:04.451
Thomas was actually killing Drill.

27:04.536 --> 27:06.937
Shh!

27:57.521 --> 27:59.406
Sean?

28:05.796 --> 28:07.314
Sean?

28:09.767 --> 28:11.518
Sean, is that you?

28:23.781 --> 28:25.115
Sean?

28:27.902 --> 28:30.837
Who's in there?

28:30.921 --> 28:32.589
[Breathing heavily]

28:45.402 --> 28:47.203
[Door closes in distance]

28:50.174 --> 28:51.307
[Door locks]

28:51.408 --> 28:53.243
Maria: No.

28:55.429 --> 28:57.981
Who's in there?! Open the door!

28:58.065 --> 28:59.249
Open the door!

28:59.333 --> 29:01.000
[Pounding, doorknob rattling]

29:16.016 --> 29:18.101
Hi.

29:18.185 --> 29:20.603
My friend has a question for you.

29:26.256 --> 29:28.490
[Breathing heavily]

29:28.591 --> 29:30.325
Please. Help.

29:30.393 --> 29:32.728
He's... he's here!

29:32.779 --> 29:34.196
You don't have to be afraid.

29:34.297 --> 29:35.798
He just wants to be friends.

29:37.391 --> 29:38.591
Please.

29:38.659 --> 29:40.426
Whatever he wants you to do...

29:40.494 --> 29:43.829
He wants me to ask you a question.

29:43.897 --> 29:45.831
What question?

29:49.169 --> 29:51.737
How did you kill the first one?

29:53.640 --> 29:55.825
[Thunder crashes]

29:55.909 --> 29:58.210
[Hammering]

30:25.338 --> 30:27.723
Thomas, where are you?!

30:27.807 --> 30:30.793
[Thunder rumbles]

30:32.696 --> 30:35.548
Thomas, what are you doing in there?!

30:47.861 --> 30:49.378
It's this one.

30:54.934 --> 30:57.269
Lena: What is it?

30:59.005 --> 31:00.139
It's how he did it.

31:00.190 --> 31:02.958
Thomas: Drill is not your friend.

31:03.009 --> 31:07.679
He's just using you to get what he wants,

31:07.780 --> 31:09.231
like he used me.

31:09.315 --> 31:11.183
That's not true.

31:11.251 --> 31:13.235
Drill fixed my heart,
and now I'm all better.

31:13.286 --> 31:15.854
And... and... and now he...
he wants you to do something.

31:15.922 --> 31:17.889
All you have to do is answer the question.

31:17.924 --> 31:21.393
It's easy. Please don't make him mad.

31:21.477 --> 31:22.611
[Gasping]

31:22.729 --> 31:23.662
Open the door!

31:23.796 --> 31:27.332
Open the door!

31:27.400 --> 31:29.401
No.

31:29.502 --> 31:32.070
Open the door!

31:34.140 --> 31:35.807
Tell him he'll never get it out of me.

31:35.875 --> 31:38.810
[Indistinct whispering]

31:38.895 --> 31:41.646
Drill's not happy hearing that.

31:42.899 --> 31:43.832
What happened?

31:43.916 --> 31:45.967
The light... they all came on.

31:46.052 --> 31:48.220
When I came out to check, someone ran in.

31:48.254 --> 31:50.672
Hold this.

31:50.757 --> 31:51.857
Thomas: Yeah?

31:51.924 --> 31:54.125
Well, you can tell Drill to go to hell.

31:54.227 --> 31:55.627
That's a bad word.

31:55.695 --> 31:57.162
I'm not allowed to say that.

31:57.230 --> 31:58.430
You don't have to.

31:58.498 --> 31:59.898
I'm sure he heard me.

32:04.353 --> 32:06.254
Maria: Open the door!

32:08.841 --> 32:10.141
Open the door!

32:11.394 --> 32:13.044
What are you doing?

32:17.817 --> 32:20.835
Drill says you have one more chance.

32:20.920 --> 32:22.420
Tell him.

32:25.741 --> 32:26.858
[Sniffles]

32:26.959 --> 32:28.943
[Voice breaking]
He took everything from me.

32:30.529 --> 32:33.431
He took my brother.

32:33.516 --> 32:36.968
He took my family.

32:39.238 --> 32:41.756
There's nothing left to take!

32:44.207 --> 32:45.457
He says there's one more thing.

32:45.591 --> 32:47.576
No!

32:49.362 --> 32:52.197
I know what it feels like
to cross that line.

32:52.265 --> 32:57.135
After this, you'll never be innocent again.

32:59.438 --> 33:04.176
[Machinery beeps, whirs]

33:04.260 --> 33:05.810
[Indistinct whispering]

33:05.895 --> 33:08.513
[Screaming]

33:08.581 --> 33:10.682
Young Thomas: I know how to do it!

33:10.766 --> 33:12.951
I know how I'm gonna send
my friend's signal!

33:13.002 --> 33:15.887
Yeah? And how are you gonna do that?

33:15.988 --> 33:18.857
I built something. It's in there.

33:18.958 --> 33:20.258
What?

33:20.342 --> 33:22.444
You have to see for yourself.

33:22.528 --> 33:23.728
What is it?

33:23.796 --> 33:26.581
It's like a satellite, sort of.
The same idea, at least.

33:26.665 --> 33:28.516
How does it work?

33:28.634 --> 33:29.901
You have to go inside to see.

33:29.985 --> 33:32.370
Trust me. This is gonna work.

33:34.006 --> 33:35.190
[Thunder crashes]

33:51.240 --> 33:52.574
Hey!

33:54.293 --> 33:55.643
Thomas, let me out of here.

33:55.728 --> 33:57.712
You're not Eliot. I know you're not.

33:57.796 --> 33:58.880
What are you talking about? Of course I am.

33:58.964 --> 34:01.265
No! You killed him, Drill!
You took Eliot away!

34:01.333 --> 34:03.334
I don't know what you're talking about!

34:03.402 --> 34:08.188
I'm not Drill! Come on!
You have to believe me!

34:08.306 --> 34:10.742
Eliot?

34:10.876 --> 34:12.560
It's me.

34:12.678 --> 34:14.911
I'm your brother.

34:15.013 --> 34:16.813
[Thunder rumbles]

34:16.915 --> 34:18.216
You're not him.

34:18.317 --> 34:20.168
[Electricity crackling]

34:20.284 --> 34:22.469
Let me out! [Groans]

34:26.458 --> 34:28.893
Thomas.

34:29.027 --> 34:31.712
It doesn't matter, Thomas.

34:31.830 --> 34:33.898
The others.

34:33.998 --> 34:36.333
They will come.

34:56.204 --> 34:58.406
[Screaming]

34:58.991 --> 35:00.324
[Thomas screaming]

35:00.459 --> 35:01.909
No! No!

35:01.993 --> 35:03.210
God!

35:03.328 --> 35:05.496
Okay. Wait, wait, wait!

35:05.630 --> 35:06.464
[Grunts]

35:06.548 --> 35:10.668
Okay. Okay. Okay. It's okay.

35:10.802 --> 35:12.803
Come on, Thomas. Stay with us.

35:15.140 --> 35:17.041
You stay with us, Thomas.

35:17.142 --> 35:19.510
Okay? You don't go anywhere.
You stay with us, you hear?

35:19.644 --> 35:21.979
You hear me? Stay with us.

35:27.492 --> 35:32.128
Wes: This is how he did it.

35:32.163 --> 35:33.296
He lured his brother here

35:33.364 --> 35:35.999
knowing the lightning was gonna strike.

35:36.100 --> 35:39.002
And when it did...

35:41.622 --> 35:43.773
Claire: The lightning
may have killed Drill.

35:45.726 --> 35:47.877
But Eliot...

35:48.813 --> 35:50.947
He was gone the moment that son of a bitch

35:51.048 --> 35:52.048
took his body.

36:00.941 --> 36:02.759
Lena: I don't understand.

36:02.793 --> 36:06.796
If Drill can possess a child,
why hasn't he done it yet?

36:06.897 --> 36:08.414
What is he waiting for?

36:08.532 --> 36:12.035
The right host.

36:12.102 --> 36:13.169
Like the Rabbi said,

36:13.204 --> 36:14.854
once he makes his choice, it's permanent.

36:17.575 --> 36:20.610
He's looking for someone useful.

36:23.380 --> 36:24.814
We have to stop him.

36:24.899 --> 36:26.516
We have to stop him.

36:26.617 --> 36:28.885
Wes: How can we stop him?

36:28.986 --> 36:32.922
The one way we know how to kill Drill...

36:33.023 --> 36:36.059
Is after he's taken a child.

36:36.126 --> 36:37.460
[Sniffles]

36:37.594 --> 36:40.063
[Screams]

37:07.241 --> 37:08.791
Frommer.

37:11.411 --> 37:13.479
He can never know about this.

37:15.499 --> 37:16.866
If he finds out...

37:16.934 --> 37:21.988
Henry, Minx...

37:22.072 --> 37:23.758
None of them will ever be safe.

37:23.776 --> 37:26.711
♪ Death may come invisible ♪

37:29.989 --> 37:35.077
♪ or in the holy wall of fire ♪

37:35.079 --> 37:40.033
♪ in the breath between the markers ♪

37:40.123 --> 37:44.194
♪ on some black I-80 mile ♪

37:44.213 --> 37:47.232
♪ from the madness of the governments ♪

37:50.853 --> 37:55.907
♪ to the vengeance of the sea ♪

37:55.975 --> 38:00.495
♪ well, everything is eclipsed ♪

38:00.580 --> 38:03.565
♪ by the shape of destiny ♪

38:05.117 --> 38:07.552
♪ so love me now ♪

38:07.636 --> 38:11.323
♪ ohhhhhh ♪

38:11.424 --> 38:13.258
♪ hell is coming ♪

38:13.342 --> 38:16.828
♪ ohhhhhh ♪

38:16.896 --> 38:18.780
You can rest now, Thomas.

38:18.864 --> 38:21.049
♪ Kiss my mouth ♪

38:21.133 --> 38:23.902
He won't hurt you anymore.

38:24.003 --> 38:26.971
♪ Hell is here ♪

38:31.243 --> 38:34.829
♪ see the sterile soil ♪

38:34.880 --> 38:38.516
♪ poisoned sky ♪

38:38.617 --> 38:43.738
♪ final scraps of life ♪

38:43.822 --> 38:48.309
♪ bringing new tears ♪

38:56.769 --> 39:02.607
♪ I'm leaving this place ♪

39:03.158 --> 39:07.645
♪ but there's nothing
I'm planning to take ♪

39:09.682 --> 39:11.649
♪ just you ♪

39:13.318 --> 39:15.219
♪ just you ♪

39:16.188 --> 39:19.006
♪ just you ♪

39:23.495 --> 39:27.014
♪ just you ♪

39:35.641 --> 39:37.024
[Door opens]

39:40.345 --> 39:41.812
[Door closes]

39:45.934 --> 39:47.785
Mr. President.

39:47.853 --> 39:49.720
Sorry for interrupting your weekend.

39:49.821 --> 39:51.022
No, I know you, Haley.

39:51.123 --> 39:52.423
I know you wouldn't be here

39:52.491 --> 39:53.691
if it wasn't important.

39:53.742 --> 39:54.825
Sit.

39:59.498 --> 40:01.198
[Sighs]

40:02.367 --> 40:04.051
[Sniffs]

40:04.136 --> 40:07.004
Mr. President, uh...

40:07.105 --> 40:10.007
Tonight we learned

40:10.058 --> 40:13.511
how to kill this alien entity
that calls itself Drill.

40:13.612 --> 40:15.262
How?

40:15.380 --> 40:19.083
We believe he can possess
the body of a child.

40:19.184 --> 40:23.020
Now, we aren't quite sure yet
how that works,

40:23.071 --> 40:27.691
but once he does, he can be destroyed.

40:27.792 --> 40:29.927
So what you're saying to me is...

40:30.061 --> 40:34.765
the life of one child
for the lives of many.

40:34.833 --> 40:37.901
Quite possibly for the lives of all.

40:40.071 --> 40:43.357
It involves a grave sacrifice, sir.

40:43.441 --> 40:46.210
Which is why I have to
ask you, Mr. President,

40:46.311 --> 40:50.781
do you think you're capable, truly capable,

40:50.882 --> 40:53.517
of making this decision?

41:06.464 --> 41:08.098
[Indistinct whispering]

